Divested businesses[edit]
Hardware and home improvement (HHI)[edit]
These were sold to Spectrum Brands in 2012.

Baldwin â acquired in 2010
Kwikset â acquired in 1989 by Black & Decker
National Hardware â general hardware; acquired in 2005
Price Pfister â plumbing fixtures; acquired in 1989 by Black & Decker
Weiser Lock â keyless entry and door hardware

Air compressors and pressure washers[edit]
This was sold to MAT Holdings in 2011.[35]

DeVilbiss Air Power â pneumatic tools; B & D acquired in 2004;[29] now known as MAT Industries, LLC

Tools[edit]

Husky â private-label hand tools for The Home Depot; acquired in 1986, later transferred to The Home Depot
Craftsman â private-label hand tools for Sears, up until the mid-1980s. Reacquired by Stanley in 2017
Vector Products â battery chargers, power inverters, and similar power products; acquired in 2007; sold to Baccus Global in 2010

